the primary settlement in town, where 1,108 people resided at the 2010 census, is defined as the greenville census-designated place (cdp) and is located at the junction of   routes 31, 45, and 123. once a part of mason called mason village, greenville is one of the state's est and smallest towns, incorporated in 1872. it is located at the high falls on the souhegan river, whose plentiful water power provided the mill town with the state's first industries, making cotton and woolen goods.